Supp vs. Keusing. 1. A parol lease of premises, from the owner, is a perfectly good defense to any proceedings to eject the lessee summarily, or to an action to recover the possession of the land. 2. Against unlawful violence the tenant has the protection of magistrates and the police, if unable to resist it by himself alone. A court of equity is not a proper tribunal to prevent or redress such wrongs. at special term, February —, 1866.)

(Before Robertson, Ch. J.
